 {"id":"bd-1qkni","title":"Diagram Color Themes & Style Presets","description":"## Goal
Add named color palettes for diagram rendering (e.g., "default", "corporate", "neon", "monochrome", "pastel", "high-contrast") that remap node fills, edge colors, cluster backgrounds, and text colors.

## Why
- Visual polish with minimal effort. Color is the cheapest way to make diagrams look professional.
- Different contexts need different palettes: documentation (corporate), presentations (neon), accessibility (high-contrast), printing (monochrome).
- The IR already carries style_refs; this adds a palette layer on top.
- Users can cycle themes in the demo showcase with a keybinding.

## Palette Definitions
Each palette defines:
- node_fill: [Color; 8] — one per NodeShape or cycling through nodes
- node_border: Color
- node_text: Color
- edge_color: Color
- edge_label_color: Color
- cluster_fill: Color (low opacity)
- cluster_border: Color
- background: Color
- accent: Color (for selection/highlighting)

## Preset Palettes
1. Default: blue nodes, gray edges (current behavior)
2. Corporate: navy/teal/gray, professional look
3. Neon: cyan/magenta/green on dark background, high contrast
4. Monochrome: white/gray/black only, works on any terminal
5. Pastel: soft muted colors, easy on eyes
6. High-contrast: WCAG AAA compliant, bold primary colors

## Files
- crates/ftui-extras/src/mermaid_render.rs (add DiagramPalette struct + preset palettes)
- crates/ftui-extras/src/mermaid.rs (add palette selection to MermaidConfig)
- crates/ftui-demo-showcase/src/screens/mermaid_showcase.rs (keybinding to cycle themes)

